    "attributes": {
        "action": "Use Centre-Assessed-Grades for the 2021 A-Level, AS Level and GCSE grades.",
        "additional_details": "Students from across the country have been provided with different access to online learning. Many students feel that they cannot achieve their full potential. Centre-assessed-grades (teacher assessment) backed up with course work evidence enables all students to have an equal chance of reaching their earned grade.",
        "background": "This petition calls on the government to scrap the planned use of 'mini-assessments' and instead revert to a system of centre-assessed-grades. These could be backed up with evidence and coursework from the students' entire learning period.",
